        {
          "elementId"    :"ch01-el02",
          "type"         :"text",
          "subtype"      :"intro",
          "format"       :"HTML",
          "text"         :"The letter of Jude is short but urgent. Written to believers facing false teaching, it calls Christians to stand firm in the truth. Jude reminds us that the gospel is not something to move beyond — it is something to defend and hold onto.<br><br>As we begin, we’ll see both the security believers have in God and the responsibility they have to contend for the faith.",
          "bottomPadding":"normal"
        },

        {
          "elementId"    :"ch01-el03",
          "type"         :"heading",
          "subtype"      :"subsection",
          "level"        :"2",
          "format"       :"plainText",
          "text"         :"Read Jude 1–2",
          "bottomPadding":"normal"
        },

        {
          "elementId"    :"ch01-el04",
          "type"         :"text",
          "subtype"      :"bridge",
          "format"       :"HTML",
          "text"         :"Jude begins not by focusing on problems, but on God’s work in his people.",
          "bottomPadding":"normal"
